            <p class="desc_comp_tav">&emsp;&emsp; <b>Q: How many people are allowed to be sent for each competition from each University/Institute?</br></br></b>"There are no specific rules, but each team <b>could only submit one work</b> to one of the Epicentrum competition. One University is not limited to send how many team or participants, with the requirement that every team/team members are different for each competition."</p>
            <p class="desc_comp_tav">&emsp;&emsp; <b>Q: Are Commoviecator competitions done individually or as a team?</br></br></b>"Commoviecator competitions are done as a team, consisting of several people who are involved as a film crew. The crew consists of students from the same university, represented by one person to collect and upload the files needed for the Commoviecator."</p>
            <p class="desc_comp_tav">&emsp;&emsp; <b>Q: What if the participating team for the Commoviecator competition has more than 3 members?</br></br></b>"The filmmaker teams that participate in Commoviecator are allowed to have more than 3 film crews. We do not have any limitation of how many film crews are allowed to participate for each team."</p>
